OL,7,FResponding to the report, Ms Robison
OL,8,Fsaid: "This report rightly recognises
OL,9,Fthat Scotland's finances remain
OL,10,Flargely dictated by the UK
OL,11,FGovernment's spending decisions,
OL,12,Firrespective of the impact on Scottish
OL,13,Fpublic services.
OL,15,F"That has meant Scotland has been left
OL,16,Fwith a shortfall of #400 million to
OL,17,Fpay for the Chancellor's national
OL,18,Finsurance increase, and saw Scotland
OL,19,Fshort-changed by more than a billion
OL,20,Fpounds over the next three years at
OL,21,Fthe recent spending review.
OL,26,@pD@GOUwD@AOU
